  "description": "<p>We've all said it: I wish I didn't need to get out of the sleeping bag. Wish no more! The Original Selk'bag is one part sleeping bag and one part puffy onesie, with separate legs and arms so you can go straight from the air mattress to making coffee. Elastic hand enclosures seal out drafts (like those on infant snow suits, but adult-sized), and removable booties let you slip into sturdier footwear while still wearing your bag. The fabric, insulation and zippers are made from 230 discarded plastic bottles, helping to reduce waste and make a more sustainable planet.</p><ul><li>Two layers of 120gsm recycled hollow-fibre insulation mimic down clusters for high warmth to weight</li><li>Balaclava-style face mask adds warmth and protection against the cold</li><li>Elastic hand closures seal out drafts</li><li>Zippered leg vents help regulate temperature and allow access to pant pockets</li><li>Zip-off booties have nylon bottoms for durability</li><li>Side cargo pocket and front kangaroo pocket</li></ul>",
